Here's a minimal API endpoint handling multipart form uploads with multiple images and a description:

```csharp
// Program.cs

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size (default is ~30MB)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    var form = await request.ReadFormAsync(new FormOptions
    {
        MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 50 * 1024 * 1024
    });

    var description = form["description"].ToString();
    var files = form.Files.GetFiles("images");

    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No images provided.");

    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        if (!file.ContentType.StartsWith("image/"))
            return Results.BadRequest($"'{file.FileName}' is not an image.");

        var path = Path.Combine("uploads", $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{Path.GetExtension(file.FileName)}");
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(path);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream);
        saved.Add(path);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { description, fileCount = saved.Count, paths = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery();          // required for minimal APIs accepting form data without a token

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **Kestrel limit** — `MaxRequestBodySize` must be raised; it defaults to ~28.6 MB.
- **`FormOptions.MultipartBodyLengthLimit`** — controls the per-request multipart size (default 128 MB, but Kestrel's body limit kicks in first).
- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — needed in .NET 8+ because minimal APIs now enforce antiforgery on form-bound endpoints by default.
- Form fields and files share the same `multipart/form-data` body — `form["description"]` reads the text part, `form.Files.GetFiles("images")` reads all file parts named `images`.

**Test with `curl`:**

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/upload \
  -F "description=vacation photos" \
  -F "images=@photo1.jpg" \
  -F "images=@photo2.png"
```
